Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.84,0:00:07.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Professor Agasa took us to a hot spring inn in Hakone.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.89,0:00:13.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The filming for the newest movie in the Blood\NSpray Hitman series was taking place there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.72,0:00:15.99,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,We came across the scriptwriter Tetsuyama Ganji-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.57,0:00:15.99,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\blur2\be5\fad(250,0)\3c&H6B354C&}Tetsuyama Ganji (67)\NScriptwriter
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.71,0:00:19.45,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The actress playing the heroine, Natori Mishio-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.28,0:00:19.45,Signs,,0,0,0,,Natori Mishio (28)\NActress
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.23,0:00:22.71,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Her manager, Tanzawa Junsaku-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.75,0:00:22.70,Signs,,0,0,0,,Tanzawa Junsaku (34)\NMishio's Manager
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.41,0:00:26.92,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,And the lead actor, Teradou Unpei-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.96,0:00:26.92,Signs,,0,0,0,,Teradou Unpei (33)\NActor
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.08,0:00:31.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At dawn the next day, we went to the laketop outdoor spa...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.03,0:00:35.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only to discover the murderer Tetsuyama-san in the women's bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.22,0:00:43.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Judging from the circumstances, the culprit likely waited\Noutside the bathhouse all night to ambush Tetsuyama-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.66,0:00:46.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after the crime, blended into the crowd.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.98,0:00:53.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only guests who walked around alone the night before were...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.35,0:00:57.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mishio-san, Tanzawa-san, and Teradou-sanâ€”those three people.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.98,0:01:00.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is likely...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.36,0:01:03.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To be among those three.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.05,0:01:24.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we continue lamenting the passing seasons...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.87,0:01:26.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We'll be unable to confront the mysteries of cases!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.85,0:01:28.48,Dialogue,,0,0,5,,One actor got caught in a pitfall.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.50,0:01:30.36,Dialogue,,0,0,5,,The mysteries of the bathroom is finally revealed!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.56,0:01:32.22,Dialogue,,0,0,5,,{\fscy120\fscx120\fad(0,0)\bord0.1}Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.23,0:01:34.02,Dialogue,,0,0,5,,{\fscy120\fscx120\fad(0,0)\bord0.1}The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.02,0:01:36.30,Dialogue,,0,0,5,,{\fscy120\fscx120\fad(0,50)\bord0.1}His name is: Detective {\t(1450,1451,\shad0\1c&H4331B1&)}Conan{\1c&H6AE8FA&}!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.74,0:03:08.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, the culprit has to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.11,0:03:10.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This woman right here!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.41,0:03:15.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Last night, I overheard Tetsuyama-sensei\Ntalking on his phone in the lobby.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.08,0:03:18.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saying things like you had finally come around...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.62,0:03:21.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the laketop outdoor spa with the morning sun shining...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.63,0:03:25.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that if the lead actor didn't please you, he could make a switch!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.84,0:03:30.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Surely she must've used her feminine wiles\Nto lure Tetsuyama-sensei here and...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.68,0:03:31.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.97,0:03:35.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That would make sense with him being dead in the women's bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.56,0:03:36.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.85,0:03:39.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were you the other party on the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.65,0:03:42.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.69,0:03:45.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told him that, if he came to the women's\Nbath first thing in the morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.28,0:03:48.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd take a dip with him before the other guests arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.99,0:03:50.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that was just a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.86,0:03:56.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only wanted to teach that perverted sensei a lesson\Nby making him wait in vain and embarrass himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.66,0:04:01.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Given that I wasn't the only actress who\Nwas sick to death of his sexual harassment!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.42,0:04:07.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, it seems you both\Nhad motives to kill Tetsuyama-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.09,0:04:09.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.80,0:04:11.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This guy here has a motive, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.05,0:04:15.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Five years ago, Tetsuyama-sensei suddenly\Ntook his lead role in the movie away from him...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.97,0:04:17.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he hasn't acted ever since then!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.64,0:04:20.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.19,0:04:21.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.35,0:04:23.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did resent him a bit at the time...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.94,0:04:25.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But now I'm thankful.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.19,0:04:30.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's thanks to him that I was able to experience\Nvarious things besides being an actor.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.15,0:04:32.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.24,0:04:34.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't hate him enough to kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.08,0:04:35.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Me neither!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.04,0:04:37.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yokomizo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.37,0:04:41.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was found behind a basket in the changing room.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.17,0:04:43.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A Japanese green tea plastic bottle?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.46,0:04:47.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But what's inside doesn't look like green tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.71,0:04:48.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.80,0:04:50.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like normal water.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.92,0:04:55.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, we found match cinders floating on\Nthe surface of the lake near the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.93,0:04:57.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Match cinders?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.27,0:04:59.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.47,0:05:00.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uhm...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.81,0:05:08.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not have those three people meet with the employees\Nwho were at the entrance to the bridge in the main building?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.15,0:05:10.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.57,0:05:15.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the culprit hid here all night, they wouldn't\Nhave passed through the entrance yet today, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.78,0:05:23.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because this floor is dimly lit and rather\Ndark until about 6:00 in the morning...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.75,0:05:27.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And police officers and all sorts of\Npeople have passed through today...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.10,0:05:28.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We couldn't identify anyone specific.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.96,0:05:35.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although we do remember Tetsuyama-sensei\Ncoming first, and then the children came after him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.84,0:05:41.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said Tetsuyama-sensei was specifically allowed to\Nenter the outdoor spas before everyone else, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.07,0:05:41.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Had it always been that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.43,0:05:45.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, because sensei enjoys taking the very first bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.94,0:05:53.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So when sensei stays here, we always turn the lights\Nin the bath on at 4:30 AM to let him through early.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.71,0:05:55.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.99,0:05:58.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It appears that one of the victim's rings has gone missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.37,0:06:00.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.45,0:06:03.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, only an empty case was left in his room...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.21,0:06:08.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the case says it's the Nichiuri TV's Newcomer Scenario Award.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.25,0:06:13.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean that ring with the soybean-sized jewel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.76,0:06:16.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, right, the silver one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.13,0:06:18.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before giving lectures or party speeches...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.18,0:06:22.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He used to wear it, claiming it was\Nhis good-luck charm for the occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.93,0:06:24.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't find it anywhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.27,0:06:24.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.56,0:06:28.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Presumably it was thrown into the lake along with the weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.48,0:06:32.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you didn't find anything in these three people's room?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.44,0:06:34.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we found something in each of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.24,0:06:39.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the ashtray of Teradou-san's room, we\Nfound a large number of match cinders.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.37,0:06:41.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Matches, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.45,0:06:43.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.08,0:06:44.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I merely used the matches to light my cigarettes!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.12,0:06:50.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a glove in a bag in Tanzawa-san's room,\Nbut for some reason there was only the left one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.88,0:06:52.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a golf glove.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.88,0:06:56.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are many people who wear it solely\Non their left hand to prevent slipping.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.59,0:06:58.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm right-handed after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.80,0:07:03.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, in the trashcan in Natori-san's\Nroom, there was a broken wine glass...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.39,0:07:06.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And on top of the desk was a script\Nwith some of the pages crumbled.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.15,0:07:09.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was for the role.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.81,0:07:15.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I was reading the script last night, I got to a scene where\Nmy character ripped out paper and threw a glass at someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.49,0:07:20.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I did it without realizing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.53,0:07:25.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Putting myself in character and acting\Nout my role is how I do business.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.66,0:07:28.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Put oneself in character and act it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.75,0:07:32.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, so that's how it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.80,0:07:37.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person was completely absorbed in their role and forgot that...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.47,0:07:43.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The conclusive evidence is still hidden in their own pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.20,0:07:45.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Yokomizo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.73,0:07:49.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've spoken with the inn employees at the front desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.65,0:07:50.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.52,0:07:55.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They said that, at around 5:30 this morning, Natori-san\Nturned her room key in, which remains at the front desk.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.07,0:08:03.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, at about 2:00, Teradou-san called the employees\Nto his room, stating that his air conditioner was broken.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.91,0:08:06.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, turned out to be user error.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.83,0:08:11.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what about Tanzawa-san getting\Nchange at the front desk at about 4:30?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.25,0:08:12.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was also confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.96,0:08:15.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They said he exchanged a 1000-yen bill for 100-yen coins.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.22,0:08:23.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before we police came, was there really not even a single\Nperson who went back to the main building from that bridge?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.80,0:08:24.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.35,0:08:30.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, these three people would've\Nbeen in the main building until dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.14,0:08:34.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And about "the culprit hiding themselves at\Nthe laketop outdoor spa the entire night"...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.02,0:08:37.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That speculation from this brat was completely off the mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.15,0:08:38.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.95,0:08:44.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.03,0:08:44.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.24,0:08:51.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, surely the culprit infiltrated\Nthe outdoor spa from the lake...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.96,0:08:55.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after murdering Tetsuyama,\Nthey returned to the lake and fled.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.25,0:08:57.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.34,0:08:59.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Start gathering intel from the lake's perimeter-
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.30,0:09:01.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no need for that, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.47,0:09:05.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the murderer is still here...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.56,0:09:08.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right in front of my eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.52,0:09:20.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.65,0:09:23.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything about this murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.90,0:09:26.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, just pretend to talk along with my voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.90,0:09:27.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.24,0:09:29.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Butting in all of a sudden!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.45,0:09:31.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I'm just...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.87,0:09:37.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just saying that, despite there being surviving traces of\Nsomeone having hidden at the outdoor spa overnight...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.91,0:09:41.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you guys blind enough not to see them?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.13,0:09:42.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Traces, you say.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.79,0:09:47.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The plastic tea bottle in the changing room\Nwhich curiously contained water inside...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.34,0:09:50.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the match cinders that were\Nfloating on the lake are such traces.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.43,0:09:58.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To wait outside the bathhouse overnight as the wind rampages\Nacross the lake is too cold to bear in a season like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.73,0:10:01.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having said that, even if someone were\Nto enter the bathhouse from the veranda...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.98,0:10:06.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They wouldn't be able to bear the cold night in the\Nchanging room where the lights and heat were both off.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.53,0:10:10.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's only one way to stay warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.15,0:10:13.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying someone soaked in the hot spring?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.28,0:10:14.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.83,0:10:21.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Judging from the fact they drank up not only the green tea\Nbut also the water from the changing room sink as refills...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.42,0:10:23.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They must've taken multiple dips overnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.50,0:10:27.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because one gets thirsty just from being in the bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.59,0:10:30.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the match cinders floating in the lake...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.84,0:10:33.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone has been smoking in order to stay awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.01,0:10:37.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They must've done so at the veranda in\Norder to not make the spa smell like smoke.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.47,0:10:42.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, you with the cigarettes are the most suspicious one!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.40,0:10:43.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey how, I didn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.19,0:10:47.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only said that they were smoking...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.15,0:10:49.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not that they were smoking cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.03,0:10:54.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't cigarettes, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.12,0:10:55.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pipe...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.87,0:10:57.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.49,0:11:00.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you mean they were smoking a pipe while waiting...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.04,0:11:01.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.58,0:11:07.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one hiding at the laketop outdoor spa all night was...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.00,0:11:10.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim of the murder, Tetsuyama-san himself!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.38,0:11:16.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what about the "Tetsuyama-san" who\Npassed through this entrance at 4:30 this morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.56,0:11:19.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.43,0:11:21.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were impersonating Tetsuyama-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.94,0:11:27.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, by reversing the common\Nsense that there'd be no reason for the victim...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.11,0:11:30.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To hide at the would-be crime scene for a\Nlong period of time waiting for the culprit...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.44,0:11:33.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They set up a mind trick to throw us off!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.61,0:11:36.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.24,0:11:39.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you guys let Tetsuyama-san pass\Nthrough this entrance to the outdoor spa?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.17,0:11:41.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.37,0:11:43.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I really think it was him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.00,0:11:46.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The unique way he walked...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.50,0:11:51.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the stern expression he had as if coercing us were\Nmanners that could only belong to Tetsuyama-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.71,0:11:55.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, this floor was dimly lit at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.18,0:11:56.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention that person...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.14,0:12:02.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was wearing a knit cap and glasses, and had\Na towel wrapped around like a scarf, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.23,0:12:06.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.90,0:12:09.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,People who knew Tetsuyama-san very well...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.65,0:12:11.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Such as this actor...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.11,0:12:13.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that former actor...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.20,0:12:17.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could have acted out the part of Tetsuyama-san, isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.74,0:12:19.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.62,0:12:22.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case, this actress here is also suspicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.41,0:12:26.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she put on many layers of clothing,\Nshe could imitate his physique.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.96,0:12:29.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And by imitating a stern expression,\Nshe wouldn't have to say anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.54,0:12:35.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She also said if he came to the women's bath first thing in the\Nmorning, she'd bathe with him before the other guests arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.43,0:12:41.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If her instruction was actually "to hide in\Nthe women's bath all night," then it all fits!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.18,0:12:43.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That would certainly be the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.93,0:12:48.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But only if the other party on the phone\Nwith Tetsuyama-san was really her.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.27,0:12:51.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Really her"?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.11,0:12:52.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying she's lying?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.86,0:12:55.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she hadn't said that, she would've\Nbeen unable to protect the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.82,0:13:01.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the one who saw Tetsuyama-san\Ntalking on the phone was Teradou-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.03,0:13:05.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Natori-san completely denied being\Nthe other party on the phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.08,0:13:07.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the suspicion would fall on the remaining person.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.83,0:13:11.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Natori-san's manager, Tanzawa-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.38,0:13:14.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,None other than you!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.09,0:13:16.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.59,0:13:17.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wasn't lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.97,0:13:22.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps Tanzawa-san told this to Tetsuyama-san over the phone:
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.14,0:13:27.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Natori-san will go to the laketop\Noutdoor spa first thing in the morning."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.14,0:13:32.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"If you want to see the bathing scene\Nof her, hide there and wait overnight."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.36,0:13:38.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As her manager who knows her\Nschedule, he could use such a strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.61,0:13:44.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And judging from Tetsuyama-san saying,\N"You've finally come around" over the phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.83,0:13:48.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was probably nagged by Tetsuyama-san many times about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.00,0:13:54.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course Tetsuyama-san could've come and\Nhidden in the women's bath first thing in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.38,0:14:01.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he was told that, if Natori-san knew Tetsuyama-san\Nhad gone to the spa, she'd likely be on her guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.26,0:14:06.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how Tanzawa-san convinced Tetsuyama-san\Nto hide at the veranda of the women's bath...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.56,0:14:11.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And walked towards the bathhouse as\NTetsuyama-san himself before 5:00 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.98,0:14:16.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Afterward, he put away his disguise in the changing room...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.19,0:14:20.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fast-talked Tetsuyama-san into coming inside the spa room...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.95,0:14:22.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And bludgeoned him to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.66,0:14:28.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, you had planned to reenter\Nthe bathhouse amid the confusion, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.41,0:14:33.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In case some of your hair had been left at the bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.42,0:14:33.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.34,0:14:37.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The children arrived earlier than you planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.26,0:14:39.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They not only found the body and made a commotion...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.22,0:14:42.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But also blocked the bathhouse entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.34,0:14:50.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You had wanted to cover up any traces of your being at\Nthe crime scene, but you couldn't secure an opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.23,0:14:52.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why Tanzawa-san was forced to...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.31,0:14:54.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold it, you're talking as if you saw it as it happened...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.98,0:14:56.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But do you have proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.94,0:14:58.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the proof is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.99,0:15:00.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you being so sneaky about, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.99,0:15:04.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that the bowtie that can change your voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.62,0:15:07.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you talking with the professor's voice?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.79,0:15:09.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't you speak with your own?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.41,0:15:10.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.54,0:15:14.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The professor doesn't know about the\Ncase, so he's whispering advice to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.71,0:15:16.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.09,0:15:17.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nice save, Haibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.92,0:15:18.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't sweat it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.55,0:15:22.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I won't let them peek at things they shouldn't, like you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.72,0:15:23.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Peek?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.55,0:15:28.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's what you mean, don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.93,0:15:30.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't see anything besides your butt!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.64,0:15:31.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Butt?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.60,0:15:34.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about a butt?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.98,0:15:35.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.06,0:15:36.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shoot!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.94,0:15:38.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I accidentally said that in the professor's voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.32,0:15:41.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, he shouldn't have known that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.53,0:15:45.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something that only the culprit should know,\Nbut Tanzawa-san knew it nonetheless!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.25,0:15:50.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why Tanzawa-san took the first step to enter the spa room.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.55,0:15:52.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that's my proof!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.59,0:15:59.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if the children were blocking the entrance, wouldn't\Nit be natural to want to know what was happening inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.43,0:16:02.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the crime scene was in the women's bath.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.31,0:16:07.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Normally you'd let a female go in\Nfirst to check on the situation, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.90,0:16:08.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.36,0:16:11.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Tanzawa-san knew...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.53,0:16:15.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That inside the spa room were only\NTetsuyama-san's body and the children.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.53,0:16:19.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So even if he should inevitably see the children naked...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.66,0:16:21.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't be a problem at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.17,0:16:28.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Ai-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.25,0:16:32.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like some kind of sinister aura is coming out...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.42,0:16:34.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're scary, really!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.88,0:16:36.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that your proof?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.39,0:16:37.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't make me laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.18,0:16:41.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for concrete proof, don't you know about it too?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.77,0:16:43.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thing Tanzawa-san still has on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.40,0:16:53.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the ring that you said on the spur of the moment\N"had a soybean-sized jewel" in order to protect him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.36,0:16:55.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To protect him?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.95,0:16:56.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.61,0:17:01.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For a ring with such a large jewel, it would\Nbe easily detected even if it were on a finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.66,0:17:08.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't think that the blackened\Nring on Tanzawa-san's left middle finger...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.38,0:17:10.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could possibly be that ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.71,0:17:11.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.47,0:17:15.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.89,0:17:18.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector, when you told him to show his belongings...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.35,0:17:28.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He realized that in his back left pants pocket\Nwas the ring he had forgotten to throw away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.98,0:17:32.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he put it on his middle finger\Nwhile fumbling around in his pocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.15,0:17:36.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the jewel hidden out of view in his palm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.07,0:17:40.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why go through the trouble for the ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.70,0:17:43.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because when the silver on it was sulfurized, it turned black.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.83,0:17:46.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This hot spring is a sulfur spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.29,0:17:50.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Reacting to the hydrogen sulfide and sulfur dioxide...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.55,0:17:52.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The surface turned into black-colored silver sulfide.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.55,0:17:58.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Upon seeing the blackened silver ring,\Nhe thought that it had to be taken off.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.35,0:18:03.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wanted it to look as if he had just arrived at the baths...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.10,0:18:06.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it wouldn't do if people suspected\Nthat he'd been in the spa for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.35,0:18:13.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, though if this were a highly concentrated\Nsulfur spring, it would've turned black instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.07,0:18:15.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regardless, what an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.95,0:18:17.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forgetting to throw it away...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.57,0:18:18.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He couldn't help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.91,0:18:22.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he was totally acting as Tetsuyama-sensei.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.70,0:18:28.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tetsuyama-sensei always held his pipe in\Nhis left hand, so he was probably left-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.12,0:18:32.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why you accidentally put it in your\Nback left pocket, which you normally wouldn't use.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.80,0:18:37.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fscy65\fscx65}\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\h\hbathrobe     {\c&HA5D6F0&}outer robe\N{\r}Until you threw away the {\c&HF1ECC8&}yukata{\r}, {\c&HA5D6F0&}tanzen{\r},\Nand weapon stained with blood in the lake...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.59,0:18:39.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You thought you'd put it there for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.39,0:18:42.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You also pushed the vending machine button with your left hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.85,0:18:45.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you referred to me as a "runt".
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.77,0:18:50.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means you were already mimicking\NTetsuyama-sensei by then, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.77,0:18:51.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.81,0:18:52.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a hassle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.78,0:18:56.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To act like such a narrow-minded man...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.82,0:18:58.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was something I'd never done before.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.07,0:19:00.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.57,0:19:05.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You still hold a grudge against Tetsuyama-sensei\Nfor dropping you as the lead role five years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.08,0:19:08.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, to put it simply, that was my motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.08,0:19:15.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The role I was denied was the middle-aged hitman from\NScarlet Wellspring, the one currently being remade.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.34,0:19:19.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I had gotten rave reviews for the Youth part...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.76,0:19:22.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought that surely I was to continue that role.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.14,0:19:25.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't it because he thought you were\Ntoo young at the time to play the role?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.43,0:19:29.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I thought so as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.77,0:19:32.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even sensei told me that I was too young...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.02,0:19:34.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That I didn't produce the melancholy vibe...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.32,0:19:37.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that I needed to experience various things.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.28,0:19:42.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I stopped acting and even became her manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.16,0:19:47.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I experienced the hard work of the underling\Nthat I didn't have the chance to as an actor...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.25,0:19:52.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Oh, this is what sensei had wanted to teach me," I had thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.58,0:19:56.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this time, when I learned that\NScarlet Wellspring was being remade...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.20,0:20:00.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I called sensei to beg him for the lead role, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.75,0:20:04.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei was so drunk, he didn't even\Nknow that I was the one on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.00,0:20:08.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tanzawa Junsaku in the lead role as the hitman?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.47,0:20:12.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be him, he's too good.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.43,0:20:14.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like he was in the Youth part...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.60,0:20:18.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he were praised as having superb skills that\Nsurpasses the original work again, it'd be annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.69,0:20:25.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how I pleaded, I was never\Nallowed to play the middle-aged hitman.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.86,0:20:31.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, not until sensei departed from this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.74,0:20:40.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the inspiration for my dream as an actor was the\Nblack-and-white Scarlet Wellspring I watched as a child...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.33,0:20:42.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wanted the role even if it killed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.62,0:20:48.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, when I think of it now, I suppose I wasn't cut out for the role.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.88,0:20:53.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I had truly been able to act as a\Nhitman immediately after killing sensei...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.26,0:20:57.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I wouldn't have made such a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.47,0:20:59.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mishio.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.72,0:21:02.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Play the role of the hostess with all your soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.14,0:21:05.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's an important role that will open up the breadth of your roles.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.48,0:21:09.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.28,0:21:16.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were the one who taught me that during the entire\Nfilming, I need to assume the role even in my private life.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.12,0:21:19.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who ordered the hit was the hostess herself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.41,0:21:23.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In order to conceal this fact, without batting an eyebrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.12,0:21:28.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She would go as far as to kill the hitman in cold blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.46,0:21:31.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a role...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.22,0:21:35.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I could never play with my soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.85,0:22:58.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.15,0:22:59.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't forget your belongings!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.90,0:23:00.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.52,0:23:03.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We should go buy one more souvenir!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.72,0:23:04.12,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Hey, Professor...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.14,0:23:04.88,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Come here a sec.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.15,0:23:11.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever since I changed clothes after leaving the hot\Nspring, for some reason my butt's been hurting.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.37,0:23:12.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can you check on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.60,0:23:13.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.08,0:23:19.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of the hot spring, Ai-kun went\Nto the men's bath a little while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.08,0:23:20.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.96,0:23:22.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.13,0:23:24.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said she was looking for something...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.51,0:23:28.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a little red and swollen.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.84,0:23:29.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.39,0:23:33.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's chili pepper.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.47,0:23:36.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you wash it off with water, it'll start healing soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.48,0:23:41.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inside your underpants is chili pepper powder!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.15,0:23:45.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, there's nothing to be worried about.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.53,0:23:46.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A child's naked body...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.74,0:23:50.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if you see it, there's no problem, is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.33,0:23:56.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That little...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.42,0:24:01.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone, catch him!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.17,0:24:03.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.87,0:24:04.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Move it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.11,0:24:05.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.15,0:24:08.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This guy is Kanemura.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.37,0:24:10.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a member of that fraud group, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.09,0:24:14.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The crime scene was between this\NNatsuhabara Station and Beika Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.35,0:24:16.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's near Sugame Station.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.36,0:24:21.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand how you feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.53,0:24:23.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.96,0:24:33.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.11,0:24:34.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Automatic Ticket Gate
